node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Hockey Collective on September 16, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'NEWS HOCKEY COLLECTIVE EVANDER KANE IS CONFIDENT THE NHL'S INVESTIGATION WILL EXONERATE HIM OF GAMBLING ACCUSATIONS MADE BY HIS WIFE H/T: ESPN'.

node.text:
Evander Kane sat down with Linda Cohn of ESPN to talk about his recent issues off the ice.

In the interview, Kane admitted that he has a gambling addiction and that led to him filing for bankruptcy in January. 

Kane also said he’s never bet on NHL games, never bet on his own games, nor has he ever tried to intentionally lose a game.
